<p>Now you can do it with the <a href="https://desktop.github.com/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">GitHub Desktop</a> application.</p>

<p>After launching the application</p>

<ol>
<li>Click on the project containing the branch</li>
<li><p>Switch to the branch you would like to delete</p>

<p><a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/c0ged.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/c0ged.png" alt="Switching branch"></a></p></li>
<li><p>From the "Branch" menu, select, "Unpublish...", to have the branch deleted from the GitHub servers.</p>

<p><a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/1u8oS.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/1u8oS.png" alt="Unpublish branch"></a></p></li>
<li><p>From the "Branch" menu, select, 'Delete "<em>branch_name</em>"...', to have the branch deleted off of your local machine (AKA the machine you are currently working on)</p>

<p><a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/TTuLO.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/TTuLO.png" alt="Delete local branch"></a></p></li>
</ol>
